        "rich_text_rJaBdp": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Introduction",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Among all ring styles, the Toi et Moi ring has one of the most romantic meanings. The name comes from French and translates to “You and Me.” Instead of featuring a single diamond, this ring design brings two stones together in one setting, symbolising two people connected by love. </p><p>The beauty of a <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/toi-et-moi-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Toi et Moi ring\">Toi et Moi ring</a> lies in its simplicity. Two stones sit side by side, sometimes slightly touching or leaning toward each other. Each stone represents an individual, and together they form a shared story. </p><p>Because of this symbolism, Toi et Moi rings have become increasingly popular for engagements, anniversaries, and meaningful gifts. At Lucira Jewelry, designs like the Pear & Radiant Cut Diamond Toi et Moi Ring, Portuguese Toi et Moi Ring, and <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/marquise-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Marquise \">Marquise </a>& Round Toi et Moi Ring highlight this idea of two distinct stones coming together in a balanced design.</p><p>Let’s explore why this ring style has captured so much attention in recent years.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_qw7HLy": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Romantic Meaning Behind the Toi et Moi Ring",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Romantic Meaning Behind the Toi et Moi Ring</h2>",
            "custom_id": "the-romantic",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_FczGG7": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>The central meaning of a Toi et Moi ring is two individuals united in one design.</p><p>Each stone represents a person. When the stones sit together, they symbolise a relationship built on partnership, connection, and shared experiences.</p><p>Unlike solitaire rings that focus on a single diamond, the Toi et Moi ring celebrates two equal elements coming together. This makes it especially meaningful for couples who see their relationship as a partnership.</p><p>For example, the Pear & Radiant Cut Diamond Toi et Moi Ring from Lucira pairs two different diamond shapes, showing how two unique personalities can complement each other.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
