        "rich_text_mEE3FU": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Toi et Moi Rings Feel Modern Yet Timeless",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Toi et Moi Rings Feel Modern Yet Timeless</h2><p>Although Toi et Moi rings feel modern today, the design has actually existed for centuries.</p><p>One of the most famous examples dates back to Napoleon Bonaparte, who reportedly gave a Toi et Moi ring to Joséphine in the 18th century. The ring featured two stones placed side by side — a design that symbolised their union.</p><p>Today, the style has returned to popularity because it feels both romantic and contemporary.</p><p>Rings like the Portuguese Toi et Moi Ring show how this historic concept can be reinterpreted with modern diamond shapes and elegant settings.</p>",
            "custom_id": "why-toi",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_LNV7Rq": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "The Design Naturally Creates Balance and Harmony",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>The Design Naturally Creates Balance and Harmony</h2><p>From a design perspective, Toi et Moi rings are visually interesting because they create natural balance.</p><p>Instead of one large stone dominating the ring, the two stones interact with each other.</p><p>Sometimes the stones are placed at slight angles or curves so they appear to lean toward one another. This small detail creates movement in the design.</p><p>The Hexa & Pear Diamond Toi et Moi Ring from Lucira is a good example of how two shapes can work together to form a harmonious composition.</p>",
            "custom_id": "the-design",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Couples Are Choosing Toi et Moi Rings Today",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Couples Are Choosing Toi et Moi Rings Today</h2><p>Many couples today want rings that feel personal rather than traditional.</p><p>The Toi et Moi design allows for creativity while still carrying deep symbolism.</p><p>Some couples choose stones that represent:</p>",
            "custom_id": "why-couples",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_DPQAJF": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>1.] Each partner’s birthstone<br/>2.] Two favourite diamond shapes<br/>3.] A diamond paired with a coloured gemstone<br/><br/>The 1.19ct Oval & <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/products/marquise-round-toi-et-moi-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Round Toi et Moi Ring\">Round Toi et Moi Ring</a> and Pear and Round Diamond Toi et Moi Ring are examples of designs that feel contemporary while still expressing the classic “you and me” meaning.</p><p>Because of this flexibility, the ring can feel truly personal.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
